        <mainBody>
          <article id="scheduleto">
            <section id="section-4">
              <num>4.</num>
              <heading>Power to add to Schedule. The Central Government may, by  notification in the Official Gazette, add to the Schedule any other</heading>
              <paragraph id="section-4.paragraph-0">
                <content>
                  <p>State law providing for the trial of offences by special Criminal</p>
                  <p>Courts, and any such addition shall take effect as if such law had  been included in the Schedule by this Act.</p>
                </content>
              </paragraph>
            </section>
            <section id="section-5">
              <num>5.</num>
              <heading>Repeal of Ordinance.</heading>
              <subsection id="section-5.1">
                <num>(1)</num>
                <content>
                  <blockList id="section-5.1.list1">
                    <listIntroduction>The Special Criminal Courts</listIntroduction>
                    <item id="section-5.1.list1.Jurisdiction">
                      <num>(Jurisdiction)</num>
                      <p>Ordinance, 1950 (7 of 1950), is hereby repealed.</p>
                    </item>
                  </blockList>
                </content>
              </subsection>
              <subsection id="section-5.2">
                <num>(2)</num>
                <content>
                  <p>Notwithstanding such repeal, anything done or any action  taken in the exercise of any power conferred by or under the said</p>
                  <p>Ordinance shall be deemed to have been done or taken in the exercise  of the powers conferred by or under this Act, as if this Act were in  force on the day on which such thing was done or action was taken.</p>
                </content>
              </subsection>
            </section>
